<!--
VOICING PLAN:
Holy Spirit, Ever Dwelling — G major (1 sharp: F#). Source M:8/4 split into 4/4 pairs.
The hymn is essentially in Em (vi) tonality throughout — nearly every measure returns to Em.

Non-diatonic handling:
- "Eb" annotations → vi (Em) substitution (Eb is chromatic color, Em is diatonic equivalent)
- F#7 (secondary dominant) → V(D) diatonic substitution
- "E" (III chord) → iii (Bm) diatonic

mm. 1-8: Light opening. RH 2 voices only (B4-D5 shell). LH vi "334" E3-G3-B3-E4 gives open
  Aeolian sound appropriate to the modal flavor of this Spirit hymn.
  vii°7 in m3 creates chromatic pull back to vi. ii→V→vi in mm. 7-8 typical modal cadence.

mm. 9-16: Varied repeat. Quartal "44" on vi (E4-A4-D5) in m10 for modern color.
  LH gains IVΔ (C3-E3-G3-B3 = CΔ) in m10b for richer IV sound.
  m12 RH expands vi to 4-note "334" (E4-G4-B4-E5) — broadened re-statement.

mm. 13-20: Middle section with I and V. m14 full V7 "333" in both hands.
  m20 B4 whole note = peak register of the arrangement, both hands fully voiced.

mm. 21-28: Final verse with fullest voicings. m23 vii°7 gets 4-note "333" in RH (F#4-A4-C5-E5).
  m25 I "334" RH (G4-B4-D5-G5) — highest RH chord in piece (G5 = top of range).
  m28 E1 pedal + vi "333" LH + vi "334" RH = maximum final density.

TEXTURE ARC:
mm. 1-4: Modal, sparse (2-note RH shell). Sets vi tonal center.
mm. 5-8: I and V introduced, RH fills out to 3 notes.
mm. 9-12: Quartal color (m10 vi "44"), 4-note RH appears (m12).
mm. 13-16: I→V center section, RH climbs to D5-G5 in m13/14.
mm. 17-20: ii7→V7 progression richens harmony. m20 B5 peak register.
mm. 21-28: Full re-statement, all hands fully voiced, E1 pedal cadence.
-->
